    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains univariate time-series data with synthetic generation combining multiple components: 1) Base sinusoidal pattern (2*sin(x/100)) establishing periodicity, 2) Low-frequency noise variables (a,b,c) changing at different intervals, 3) Random spikes (+10 amplitude) at 50,000 index intervals, and 4) Gaussian noise (\u03bc=0, \u03c3=0.5). The areaspline visualization was chosen to emphasize trend direction while maintaining density perception through fill opacity. Highcharts Boost module maintains performance for 500k+ points through WebGL rendering. Color choices (#4682B4 blue with 30% opacity) follow Cairo's principles for layered perception, while axis styling (slate gray titles) adheres to Tufte's data-ink ratio by minimizing decorative elements. Synthetic parameters simulate real-world signal patterns: base periodicity (100-index wavelength), nested noise components (100/1000/10000-index variations), and intermittent spikes mimicking sensor artifacts."
